AB  - Loss of nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide (NAD+) with aging may contribute to chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD). In a randomized controlled trial, we show that six weeks of boosting NAD+ levels in patients with COPD reduces airway inflammation and might affect biological aging, possibly through a reduction in cellular senescence. © Springer Nature America, Inc. 2024.
